videos.headline: LSU flea-flicker goes for 52 yards
videos.description: With all eyes on Leonard Fournette, the LSU running back tosses the ball back to quarterback Brandon Harris who then heaves it 52 yards to Malachi Dupre. LSU would score on the next play and go up 21-7 lead.

videos.headline: How did Gators' Callaway make that catch?
videos.description: Florida QB Treon Harris heaves it up to WR Antonio Callaway who reels in the ball with one hand, finding a way to stay inbounds and complete the first down. The Gators would score on the next drive and the cut the deficit to 21-14.

videos.headline: 50 yard heave scores TD for LSU
videos.description: Brandon Harris scrambles right and chucks the ball deep down field to Malachi Dupre who makes the catch and scores to put LSU up 28-14.

videos.headline: Florida ties game on punt return

videos.headline: LSU kicker more than just feet on fake FG
videos.description: LSU kicker Trent Domingue fakes the field goal attempt and tricks Florida, getting the ball from the placeholder and running in 16-yard for the touchdown. The Tigers go up 35-28 in the fourth quarter.
